# API Documentation Guide

This project uses Swagger/OpenAPI for API documentation.

## Swagger Setup
Swagger is configured in [src/main.ts](mdc:src/main.ts) and is available at the `/docs` endpoint.

## Documented Endpoints
API endpoints are documented in [endpoints.md](mdc:endpoints.md).

## Documentation Best Practices
When adding new endpoints:
1. Use `@ApiTags()` to categorize endpoints
2. Use `@ApiOperation()` to describe endpoint functionality
3. Use `@ApiParam()` to document path parameters
4. Use `@ApiQuery()` to document query parameters
5. Use `@ApiBody()` to document request body
6. Use `@ApiResponse()` to document response structure
7. Use `@ApiBearerAuth()` for authenticated endpoints

## DTO Documentation
DTOs should be documented using `@ApiProperty()` decorators to provide metadata for Swagger.
